data.description: Located in Gallatin Gateway, Montana, this charming 1920's schoolhouse is situated on 1.63+/- acres with no zoning and light covenants. This property is located just east of Hwy 191 (Gallatin Rd) and north of Gooch Hill Rd. The land is fenced and cross fenced for livestock, features a small seasonal ditch (with water rights) and the home is positioned overlooking the open farm land and views to the Bridger Mountains. The property allows for up to 3 outbuildings and the current shop is divided into a 2 car garage and insulated/heated studio workspace. The home which features a stunning wrap around deck takes in the views on 3 sides. The yard is fully fenced and cross fenced with a small loafing shed. The home features a private exterior entrance to the lower level guest unit, which has been utilized as an airbnb. The main level features an abundance of light, hardwood floors, and an open floor plan. There is one bedroom on the main and 2 additional upstairs.
